EmailTemplate.subject: One Reverse Mortgage - Pricing 7-24-2018
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hi {!Contact.FirstName},
Attached is our most current product and price sheet.
Remember that if you have a client who is over 62 years of age, they have the potential to get a reverse mortgage. There are also various scenarios where a traditional mortgage may not work but will work for a reverse mortgage.
Ms. Kim: 70 years old Home Value: $650,000 Mortgage Balance: $240,000 PITI: $1,700 Other Monthly Debt: $500 Monthly Income: $3,200 Credit Score: 650
This borrower’s DTI is going to limit their refinancing options. Even with a cash out transaction, they may not be able to get their DTI low enough for eligibility. Most likely, this borrower is not going to qualify for any forward mortgage solution. However, a borrower with this profile may be a PERFECT candidate for a reverse mortgage. This borrower can eliminate her mortgage payment (P&I), freeing up nearly $1300/month in cash flow. She can use those savings to help pay down her other debts.
When you come across borrowers where the DTI may be too high to find a forward mortgage solution, please reach out to your ORMS account executive. They can help you identify, price out, and present a reverse mortgage option to borrowers like Ms. Kim.
It is always best to run clients who are 62+ through our scenario calculator to see what they could qualify for. If you do not have access to the portal yet, please attend a training session by reaching out to me to get it scheduled.
Current Turn Times: New Registration: 30 minutes * May increase based on volume levels Submit to UW for Conditional Approval: 24 hours Conditions Review: 24 hours Clear to Close: 24 hours Docs to Closing Agent: 24 hours. * From Final HUD Approval
On Demand Reverse Mortgage Training:
Portal Tour: Self-paced webinar designed to get you familiar with our site. Here, you can run scenarios to see if a client qualifies for a reverse mortgage and access marketing collateral and more in-depth training.
Reverse Mortgage 101: Self-paced webinar designed to get you familiar with reverse mortgage eligibility requirements and all the basics you need to begin originating loans today.
Thank you for your business!
Best,
